     └─────────────────  Feedback/Response  ──────────────┘
                              Noise
```

### Model Components

| Component | Description | PM Responsibility |
|:----------|:------------|:------------------|
| **Sender** | Creates the message | Choose appropriate words/format |
| **Encode** | Convert thoughts to message | Use proper language, avoid jargon |
| **Message** | The communication itself | Clear, concise, complete |
| **Medium** | Channel used | Match medium to message type |
| **Decode** | Interpret the message | Verify understanding |
| **Receiver** | Gets the message | Actively listen |
| **Noise** | Interference | Minimize distractions |
| **Feedback** | Response/acknowledgment | Confirm understanding |

### Communication Barriers (Noise)

<ConceptGrid>
  <ConceptCard title="Physical & Technical" variant="danger">
    <strong>Barriers:</strong> Distance, poor audio, noisy environment, system failures.<br/>
    <strong>Mitigation:</strong> Better technology, quiet spaces, backup systems.
  </ConceptCard>
  <ConceptCard title="Semantic & Cultural" variant="warning">
    <strong>Barriers:</strong> Jargon, language differences, cultural norms/values.<br/>
    <strong>Mitigation:</strong> Define terms, avoid jargon, cultural awareness training.
  </ConceptCard>
  <ConceptCard title="Psychological" variant="primary">
    <strong>Barriers:</strong> Bias, emotions, stress, hostility.<br/>
    <strong>Mitigation:</strong> Active listening, empathy, conflict resolution techniques.
  </ConceptCard>
</ConceptGrid>

