##  Communication in Virtual/Distributed Teams

### Virtual Team Challenges

<ConceptGrid>
  <ConceptCard title="Logistics" variant="primary">
    <strong>Time zones:</strong> Use rotating meeting times and asynchronous tools.<br/>
    <strong>Technology:</strong> Ensure baseline infrastructure and backup plans.
  </ConceptCard>
  <ConceptCard title="Human Connection" variant="secondary">
    <strong>Isolation:</strong> Implement virtual team building and coffee chats.<br/>
    <strong>Visual Cues:</strong> Use video when possible to capture body language.
  </ConceptCard>
</ConceptGrid>

### Virtual Communication Best Practices

1. **Default to video** for meetings when possible
2. **Use asynchronous tools** for information sharing (not just meetings)
3. **Document decisions** in writing (not just verbal)
4. **Establish communication norms** (response time expectations, core overlap hours)
5. **Schedule regular touchpoints** (daily standups, weekly syncs)
6. **Create informal interaction opportunities** (virtual coffee breaks)

